<normalizedToken id="69BADFDF1FD3A2ED0FD2003750FFB1B9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the elytral apex attenuate and entire, declivital interstriae 1-3 denticulate, interstriae 2 with much fewer denticles than interstriae 1 or 3, antennal club flat, type 3, segment 1 occupying basal 1/4, and posterolateral margin of declivity costate, armed with two denticles.
</paragraph>
